# Production Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file and rename to RENDER_ENV_VARIABLES.txt
# Fill in actual values (NEVER commit the filled version)

## Core Configuration
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=10000
USE_MONGODB=true

## MongoDB
# Get from: https://cloud.mongodb.com → Connect → Connect your application
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://USERNAME:PASSWORD@CLUSTER.mongodb.net/DATABASE?retryWrites=true&w=majority

## Frontend URL
FRONTEND_URL=https://omegoo.vercel.app
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://omegoo.vercel.app

## JWT Secrets - GENERATE NEW ONES
# Generate using: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
JWT_SECRET=GENERATE_NEW_SECRET_HERE
REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET=GENERATE_NEW_SECRET_HERE
ADMIN_JWT_SECRET=GENERATE_NEW_SECRET_HERE

## JWT Expiry
JWT_EXPIRE=24h
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE=7d
ADMIN_JWT_EXPIRE=12h

## Security
BCRYPT_ROUNDS=10
SESSION_SECRET=GENERATE_NEW_SECRET_HERE

## Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100

## OTP
OTP_EXPIRE_MINUTES=5

## Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info

## Redis (Optional)
REDIS_URL=memory://localhost

---

## How to Generate Secrets:

PowerShell:
```powershell
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
```

Run this command 4 times to get secrets for:
1. JWT_SECRET
2. REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET
3. ADMIN_JWT_SECRET
4. SESSION_SECRET

---

## How to Add in Render:

1. Go to https://dashboard.render.com
2. Select your backend service
3. Click "Environment" tab
4. Add each variable above
5. Click "Save Changes"
6. Service will auto-redeploy

---

⚠️ **SECURITY WARNING:**
- NEVER commit the actual RENDER_ENV_VARIABLES.txt with real values
- Only commit this template file
- Keep actual secrets in Render dashboard only
- Use strong, randomly generated secrets
- Rotate secrets regularly
